<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - PINION REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PINION REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="9">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <para>Use
                <hotlnk document="s02009_13.xml" xrefid="f0200913">Figure 13</hotlnk>
                as a reference to assemble the pinion.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press inner pinion bearing cone onto the pinion gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200923">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200923" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200923" filename="../figg02/G0200923.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 23. Inner Pinion Cone Onto Pinion Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press roller bearing onto the pinion gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200924">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200924" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200924" filename="../figg02/G0200924.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Roller Bearing Onto Pinion Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Stake roller bearing in six places, using staking tool (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200925">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200925" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200925" filename="../figg02/G0200925.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Stake Roller Bearing in Six Places</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Make sure all cage bores are free of nicks, dirt, or any contamination.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install inner pinion bearing cup into pinion cage (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200926">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200926" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200926" filename="../figg02/G0200926.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Inner Pinion Bearing Cup Into Pinion Cage</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install outer pinion bearing cup into pinion cage (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200927">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200927" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200927" filename="../figg02/G0200927.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Outer Pinion Bearing Cup Into Pinion Cage</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge or shim stock (.0015 approx.) to ensure bearing cups are completely
                    seated in bearing bores. This is necessary for proper pinion position (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200928">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200928" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200928" filename="../figg02/G0200928.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Using Feeler Gauge</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place selective preload spacer that was removed during disassembly onto pinion (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200929">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200929" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200929" filename="../figg02/G0200929.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Place Spacer Onto Pinion</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place pinion cage onto pinion gear inner bearing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200930">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200930" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200930" filename="../figg02/G0200930.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 30. Pinion Cage Onto Bearing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install outer pinion bearing cone onto pinion (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200931">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200931" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200931" filename="../figg02/G0200931.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Outer Pinion Bearing Cone Onto Pinion</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect end yoke or flange seal surface for grooves caused by lip of seal. If grooves
                    can be detected with fingernail, it should be replaced.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install end yoke onto pinion, without seal, and tighten to 325 ft-lbs. (400 Nm) so
                    bearing preload can be checked.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Pinion cage should be rotated while tightening pinion end nut to seat and align the pinion
                            bearings.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
